data.Long Test Appointment:
Hi Mark,

Thank you for meeting with me for your Placements & Work Experience appointment today. Here is a link to our webpage with further information. Below I have listed the resources we looked through together as well as some additional information about our Lincoln Award. If you have any questions, please get in touch.  

Appointment notes 

Well done on the work on your CV and cover letter for Disney. They look great - we discussed some changes you could make to both for future applications.

 

Resources 

CV support page – This is our CV support page where you can use our AI tool to upload your CV. This will score your CV out of 100 and suggest further changes. You can also book in for a CV review with us as well as find the next CV workshop. 

CV and cover letter guide – This guide includes information on creating your CV, there is a really handy example on page 7 of a 2-page CV. Cover letter support and information can be found from page 11 onwards.  

 

Did you know that placement/ work experience hours can count towards the Lincoln Award? 

If you secure a placement or work experience, hours you work can count towards the 40 hours needed in the ‘Develop’ section of your Lincoln Award. The Lincoln Award is the University of Lincoln’s employability framework, designed to help you feel confident when articulating your skills and experiences to future employers. To start your Lincoln Award, click here! 

 

If you would like to book another appointment, please feel free to do so.  

Kind regards,

Millie
